comment.body:
This text proposal is a true statement about practically any OSS project -- and it doesn't mention the "full software stack" aspect that makes/made this work particularly challenging; your wording could equally well be applied to all OQS sub projects or be left away entirely.

And for the avoidance of doubt: I do not want to stress the aspect of volunteerism (I presume meaning people working for free/outside of employment) but of individuals going beyond their assigned tasks; this for example also includes people like @xvzcf and practically all external contributors -- of whom I don't know their employment status -- but do know about (and wanted to acknowledge with my proposal) their personal interest and commitment.
